<div id="review_2006383624" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2006383624" />
    <a title="Jocelyn Green" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6887032-jocelyn-green"><img alt="Jocelyn Green" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1538409112p2/6887032.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2006383624?book_show_action=true">Jun 13, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jocelyn Green" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jocelyn Green" href="/user/show/6887032-jocelyn-green">Jocelyn Green</a>
      </span>

          added it




        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6887032-jocelyn-green?shelf=christian-fiction">christian-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6887032-jocelyn-green?shelf=read-for-endorsement">read-for-endorsement</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2006383624" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2715299969685500315">Stunning. Many Sparrows is everything I want in a book: settings that spring to life, characters I love, rich historical context, heart-wrenching drama, timeless spiritual insights, and prose that reads like poetry. Lori Benton handles the conflicted eighteenth-century with sensitivity in this tender tale of hope and fear, faith and doubt, of loss and new life. Truly, an inspired masterpiece sure to stir the soul.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


